-- Liverpool Scouts Former PSG Striker, Mirror Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-11-11T10:06:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-11/liverpool-scouts-former-psg-striker-mirror-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Fulham Striker  Liverpool is scouting Fulham’s 17-year-old French striker
Moussa Dembele, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Three scouts for the Reds watched the former Paris Saint
Germain player score twice for Fulham’s Under-21 team last week,
according to the Mirror.  Hull to Palace  Hull striker Sone Aluko could head to Crystal Palace in
January for 2.6 million pounds ($4.2 million) after rejecting a
new contract, the  Daily Mirror  said  Palace wants to sign Aluko even though he will be sidelined
with an injury until February, the Mirror said.  Gerrard Hurt  Steven Gerrard and Liverpool teammate Daniel Sturridge may
not be fit to play in  England ’s game against  Chile  on Nov. 15,
 the Guardian  reported.  National-team captain Gerrard has a damaged hip and
Sturridge has a foot injury, the Guardian said.  London Return  Josh Pritchard will return to Fulham next month after a
loan stint at Tromso, “snubbing” the chance to stay at the
Norwegian club, the  Daily Express  reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
